RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROSELEE settled in the three and four paths the first turn, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and circled rivals in the five path of the far turn, steadily closed through the stretch and got up the final yards. MAYSVILLE MISS tapered in and took over nearing the three quarter pole and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady stretch encouragement but was caught in the final yards. IRISH SAMURAI was unprepared for the break, raced in the five path of the opening turn then bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced through the far turn about the three path then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. SHESAHUMBLEHUSTLER saved ground well back from early contention, bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and ran evenly down the lane. AT THE GATE settled in the three and four paths the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced in the seven path of the far turn, then passed some rivals in the lane. PRETTY SPECTACULAR raced off the pace in the three path, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. CHANNEL SCENT showed little response. TOUGH ONE saved ground, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then weakened the final sixteenth. EXTRA CRUNCHY rated close inside, gave chase from the three eighths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn. SUZZETTE STAR saved ground well off the pace and was distanced in the end.

ENTRY.NAME: Maysville Miss
ENTRY.COMMENT: up near 3/4,rated pace,pressured 3/8,rail far turn,caught late

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Samurai
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOBI WAN KENOBI saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole and closed to the lead three wide midway on the far turn, drifted leaving the turn but dug in for a clear lead toward the sixteenth pole and widened through later yards. GRUMPY'S BUDDY raced with the pace three wide, challenged at the three eighths pole and took a brief slim lead while between horses midway on the far turn, raced close through the upper stretch but flattened the final sixteenth. KAYLEE'S SPITFIRE entered the first turn in the three path then saved ground midway through the turn, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn, left the turn outside and came along for third nearing mid-stretch. TIME TO CHOOSE raced with the early pace two deep while between horses, took a slim lead nearing the nine sixteenths pole and came under pressure toward the seven sixteenths pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn and weakened inside the eighth pole. FUNKLE veered out leaving the gate and rounded the first turn about the four path, left the turn outside and gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and showed little in the lane. KING KJARTAN raced with the pace inside, was met approaching the nine sixteenths pole and gave chase from the half pole, but dropped back nearing the far turn and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: King Kjartan
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,met near 9/16,chased 1/2,faded into far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Time to Choose
ENTRY.COMMENT: with early pace,slim lead 9/16,met rail far turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Funkle
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered out break,outside 1/2,chased 7/16,5p far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Walker Devin D and Parrish Wallace

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MYSTIFIED settled off the pace in the three and four paths, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at a close disadvantage two deep on the far turn, took the lead leaving the eighth pole and dug in determinedly to hold off the game challenge of MASTER THIS, who saved ground off the pace and bid leaving the three eighths pole, steadily improved off the rail on the far turn, entered the stretch three wide and dueled gamely to the wire. TYLER TIME rated a short lead inside, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole and contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, was met leaving the turn then flattened the final sixteenth. BOOK OF DELANCEY stalked from the three path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four and five paths then flattened in the lane. SULEMAN rounded the first turn turns about the five path and raced outside into the backstretch, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced on in the five path of the far turn and showed little in the lane. RIGHTEOUS MAN stalked toward the inside, gave chase leaving the nine sixteenths pole and raced close through the backstretch, then flattened in the four path of the far turn. LUFTY'S KISSES race in the four path early on and was well back after a half mile. DIMMI QUANDO saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Master This
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,off rail far turn,3wd 1/8,game stretch try

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 17600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 25, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since July 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Races Where Entered For $5, 000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLAT DISCOUNT stalked the early pace off the rail, took the lead two deep into the backstretch and pulled herself clear toward the five sixteenths pole, was urged away at the rail on the far turn then steadily handled in the lane. DAT DARES GOLD ducked in leaving the gate then set the early pace inside, was met into the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but dropped back approaching the far turn and dueled through the stretch for second. MISS WILD rated close inside, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then relented in the stretch duel for second. CENTERFOLD ANGEL rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and weakened into the lane. ELITE SPEED hesitated at the break, rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole and raced in the three path of the far turn. DUSTWHIRL WONDER rounded the first turn about the six path and was never a factor. MISS HEART saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Centerfold Angel
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Shake and Bake Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Flat Discount
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,up 2d 1/2,cleared near 5/16,steady urging lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 17600. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 25, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since July 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Con sidered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FATHER WALSH chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail and dug in leaving the eighth pole, took over in later yards and raced clear toward the wire. MISCHIEVOUS JESSE tapered toward mid track and rated the pace, came under pressure and moved to the rail into the turn, dug in under steady encouragement leaving the turn, was caught in later yards but held on for second. STRETCH THE TRUTH steadied early, gave chase inside and raced near the rail on the turn, eased out toward the head of the lane and was gaining on the runner-up. ONE MORE FACTOR chased through the backstretch, raced in the three path of the turn and ran evenly in the lane. MOSS BOSS chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the five path, was carried to the outside nearing the head of the lane but came back to finish evenly. BIG HAMBONE chased, rounded the turn about the three path then flattened in the lane. LOADED SNIPER chased, rounded the turn about the four path, angled out nearing the head of the lane and weakened in the stretch. CONFUSION BABY BOY was not a factor and rounded the turn about the five path. AWESUMMER was shuffled back early and angled to the outside to give chase, then saved ground on the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Father Walsh
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,rail turn,dug in lane,up late,clear near wire

ENTRY.NAME: Awesummer
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back early,angled out,chased,saved ground turn

ENTRY.OWNER: P and H Stables and C and B Stables

ENTRY.NAME: Mischievous Jesse
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace,pressured near 1/4,dug in lane,caught late,held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 20600. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PLUNK rated off the rail on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and dug in under determined handling to take the nod in the final yards. SEAN THE HAMMER took the lead at the three quarter pole, moved inside into the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady stretch encouragement but reluctantly gave up the nod in the final yards. CRYPTIC CODE rounded the opening turn about the five path and left the turn outside, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and took the nod for third under the wire. WILLIAM'S CAUSE stalked the early pace off the rail, gave chase leaving the half mile pole but faded at the rail into the far turn. MOTIVATED SPEAKER raced well back saving ground, gave chase into the backstretch, could only improve his position and rounded the far turn off the rail. POSITRACTION saved ground off the pace, gave chase leaving the half mile pole but faded at the rail nearing the far turn. SPEIGHTY SENSE raced off the early pace about the three path and showed little response through the backstretch. COOL DUDE rounded the opening turn in the four path and showed little response leaving the turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Motivated Speaker
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back inside,chased 1/2,off rail far turn,improved position

ENTRY.NAME: Plunk
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,bid near 3/8,off rail far turn,determined,nod final yrds

ENTRY.NAME: Positraction
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased past 1/2,faded rail near far turn

ENTRY.NAME: William's Cause
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rai early,chased 1/2,faded rail into far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Sean the Hammer
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 1/4,rail turn,reluctantly ceded nod

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 25 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ DEJA BLUE took over nearing the seven sixteenths pole and rated the pace, came under pressure at the quarter pole, rounded the turn near the rail and held well under steady stretch handling. BAYTOWN JAKESTER chased through the backstretch, raced close off the rail on the turn and finished well. RUNNING VIOLENCE gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail and finished evenly to take third the final strides. LOOKATLITTLEFERRIS chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail and was outfinished for third the final strides. ADIOS SEE YA chased outside, rounded the turn in the three and four paths and showed little in the lane. DINNER BELL gave chase and raced in the five path of the turn. JAIME JAMEL raced wide on the turn. FOREVER THE BOSS gave close early chase then weakened through the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Purse 33900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 25 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRAY FOR THE U S A chased outside, raced close three wide on the turn, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and raced clear toward the wire. MERCI ROAD chased the pace and rounded the turn about the three path, dug in leaving the turn and took second later yards. COUSIN WINNIE chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path and finished evenly to take third the final yards. SHUTUPN'KISSME pressured the pace, raced close at the rail on the turn then flattened stride later yards. ALL WORKED UP gave chase, raced in the five path of the turn and finished well. GRANDIOSELY set a pressured pace through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn, was met mid-stretch and flattened later yards. FEAR THE DIVA engaged in close early chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn then weakened in the lane. LILLY SIMONE gave chase and rounded the turn about the three path.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: C TWO took a quick lead and set a pressured pace while tapering toward the inside, rounded the turn near the rail and held on well under steady stretch handling. RED LIL SHIPMENT engaged in a long duel from the start, rounded the turn at the rail and was outfinished. MYGIDGETMARIE tapered in and pressured the early pace, raced close in the three path of the turn, drifted leaving the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. PRINCESS MIA ROSE chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly in the lane. MIDSUMMER NIGHTS gave chase, rounded the turn about the four path and ran evenly down the lane. SUDDEN FLARE gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. NANNY'S MISSION chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, eased out leaving the turn and flattened. PRETTY CASTLE chased through the backstretch, raced in the six path of the turn and showed little in the lane. MIDNIGHT PASS chased, raced off the rail on the turn then weakened. JUJU saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Pass
ENTRY.OWNER: Tsiamis Arthur W and Pansiri Mihee

ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,tapered in,rail turn,held well driving
